first-contentful-paint.title: First Contentful Paint
first-contentful-paint.description: First Contentful Paint marks the time at which the first text or image is painted. [Learn more about the First Contentful Paint metric](https://developer.chrome.com/docs/lighthouse/performance/first-contentful-paint/).

largest-contentful-paint.title: Largest Contentful Paint
largest-contentful-paint.description: Largest Contentful Paint marks the time at which the largest text or image is painted. [Learn more about the Largest Contentful Paint metric](https://developer.chrome.com/docs/lighthouse/performance/largest-contentful-paint/).

speed-index.title: Speed Index
speed-index.description: Speed Index shows how quickly the contents of a page are visibly populated. [Learn more about the Speed Index metric](https://developer.chrome.com/docs/lighthouse/performance/speed-index/).

cumulative-layout-shift.title: Cumulative Layout Shift
cumulative-layout-shift.description: Cumulative Layout Shift measures the movement of visible elements within the viewport. [Learn more about the Cumulative Layout Shift metric](https://developer.chrome.com/docs/lighthouse/performance/layout-shift/).

total-blocking-time.title: Total Blocking Time
total-blocking-time.description: Sum of all time periods between FCP and Time to Interactive, when task length exceeded 50ms, expressed in milliseconds. [Learn more about the Total Blocking Time metric](https://developer.chrome.com/docs/lighthouse/performance/total-blocking-time/).

interactive.title: Time to Interactive
interactive.description: Time to Interactive is the amount of time it takes for the page to become fully interactive. [Learn more about the Time to Interactive metric](https://developer.chrome.com/docs/lighthouse/performance/interactive/).

performance.title: Performance
performance.description: These metrics encapsulate your app's performance across a number of key dimensions, all of which are reflected in the Lighthouse Performance Score.

accessibility.title: Accessibility
accessibility.description: These checks highlight opportunities to improve the accessibility of your web app. Only a subset of accessibility issues can be automatically detected so manual testing is also encouraged.

best-practices.title: Best Practices
best-practices.description: These checks highlight opportunities to improve the security, performance, and user experience of your web app.

seo.title: SEO
seo.description: These checks ensure that your page is optimized for search engine results ranking.

rendererFormattedStrings.varianceDisclaimer: Values are estimated and may vary. The [performance score is calculated from the median](https://web.dev/performance-scoring/) of all page loads in the category.
